INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (33,1,'2014-01-23 21:11:42','2014-01-23 21:11:42','<em><strong>How do I know if my injury is covered by the National Vaccine Injury Compensation Act?  </strong></em><strong></strong>\n\nIf you are trying to determine whether you are entitled to compensation under the National Vaccine Injury Compensation Act, the flowchart below may be of assistance.\n\nUnder the Act certain vaccines, such as the Trivalent Influenza vaccine (flu shot), are \"covered.\"  If you suffered an injury caused by a \"covered\" vaccine, you may be entitled to compensation from the Vaccine Injury Compensation Trust Fund.  For a complete list of the vaccines covered under the Vaccine Injury Compensation Act, please consult the Vaccine Injury Table here: <a title=\"Vaccine Injury Table\" href=\" http://www.hrsa.gov/vaccinecompensation/vaccinetable.html \">http://www.hrsa.gov/vaccinecompensation/vaccinetable.html </a><!--more-->\n\nIf you look at the Vaccine Injury Table, you will notice that there is additional information listed besides simply the types of vaccines.  The table also connects certain injuries to certain vaccines, while some vaccines are not linked to any particular injuries.  For instance, the Measles, Mumps and Rubella vaccine is linked to encephalopathy, yet the flu vaccine is not linked to any particular disease.  <strong>It is important to note that you may still recover if your injury is not listed, and in fact this is very ordinary.  </strong>One of the most common vaccine injuries, Guillain-Barre Syndrome (or the very similar Chronic Inflammatory Demyelinating Polyneuropathy (CIDP)) is caused by the flu shot, yet this condition is not listed in the Vaccine Injury Table.\n\nIf the vaccine you received is listed in the Vaccine Injury Table, but the injury is not, you may still recover.  However, in the event your injury is linked to the vaccine you received, then there is a legal presumption that the vaccine caused your injury as long as the onset of symptoms occurred within the time frame listed in the Vaccine Injury Table.  This means that the court will presume that the vaccine did cause your injury, and it will be the defendant\'s burden to prove otherwise.  We realize this may be confusing, which is why we created the flowchart below.\n\nIf you have any questions regarding vaccine injuries, the National Vaccine Injury Compensation Program, or the Vaccine Injury Table, please feel free to call us at (215) 259-8662. The call will cost you nothing but time.\n\nFor more information regarding the National Vaccine Injury Compensation Act in general, please click here: <a href=\"http://www.hrsa.gov/vaccinecompensation/index.html\">http://www.hrsa.gov/vaccinecompensation/index.html</a>\n\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" />\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" />\n\n&nbsp;','Vaccine Injury Flowchart','','inherit','open','open','','13-autosave-v1','','','2014-01-23 21:11:42','2014-01-23 21:11:42','',13,'http://myvaccineattorney.com/blog/?p=33',0,'revision','',0);
